Directions


                                            Mix first four ingredients; gradually stir in 1 tablespoon oil (mixture will be crumbly). Rub over both sides of pork chops.


                                               In a large skillet, heat remaining oil over medium heat; cook chops until a thermometer reads 145, 4-6 minutes per side. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
                                                    Yield: 4 servings. 








                                            Originally published as Basil Pork Chops in  Simple & Delicious
July/August 2006, p59                                                










